time required: 20 minutes
cuisine: North America
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/lemon-garlic-chicken-and-green-beans-63d947601010470fff073ac2
servings: 2
---

In a small #pot{}, combine @Jasmine Rice{1/2%cup}, @water{3/4%cup}, and a @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, wash and dry produce.

Trim @Green Beans{6%oz} if necessary. Peel and mince @Garlic{2%cloves}. Zest and quarter @Lemon{1}.

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{2%tsp} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add green beans and a pinch of salt and @Pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until lightly browned and softened, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Pat @Chicken Breast Strips{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with half the @Tuscan Heat Spice{1%tbsp}, salt, and pepper.

Add another drizzle of oil to pan with green beans. Add chicken; cook, stirring occasionally, until chicken is browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

In the last 2 minutes of cooking, add minced garlic, @Garlic Herb Butter{2%tbsp}, and @Butter{1%tbsp}; toss to coat. Turn off heat.

Add a squeeze of lemon juice.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}. Stir in lemon zest and half the @Sliced Almonds{1/2%oz}. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

Divide rice between bowls; top with chicken and green beans. Garnish with remaining almonds and serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.